rows.label: qst702504_msg0001
rows.name: Well, that's the last of them.

rows.label: qst702504_msg0002
rows.name: None of this makes any sense.

rows.label: qst702504_msg0003
rows.name:
What are Liberalitas monsters doing
here? It's like the whole ecosystem's
gone all out of whack.

rows.label: qst702504_msg0004
rows.name:
Wouldn't surprise me one bit.
Not with an Grail running riot.

rows.label: qst702504_msg0005
rows.name:
Monsters lose their home, so they fight
for another's territory. Then that lot
need new land. It's a vicious circle.

rows.label: qst702504_msg0006
rows.name:
So Iiran monsters are losing
their traditional habitats and
flowing into Liberalitas..

rows.label: qst702504_msg0007
rows.name:
..And they're displacing Liberalitas
monsters, who wind up here.

rows.label: qst702504_msg0008
rows.name:
Perhaps, then, we should follow this
disorder to its root Liberalitas.

rows.label: qst702504_msg0009
rows.name:
So I guess we aren't the only ones
to lose our homes because of war...

rows.label: qst702504_msg0010
rows.name:
Now each country will need to defend
itself not only against Metsu, but
from displaced monsters too.

rows.label: qst702504_msg0011
rows.name:
We have even less time
than I thought...

rows.label: qst702504_msg0013
rows.name:
Yet more monsters have shown up! And
they've gotten inside this time!

rows.label: qst702504_msg0015
rows.name:
There can't be many of
them left now. Let's give
them the coup de gr√¢ce!
